---
---

<section id="pricing">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-label"><span class="idx">04 -</span> The terms</div>
    <h2 class="heading">Straightforward, like a <em>handshake.</em></h2>
    <p class="section-sub">
      Porvi is a tiny thing run for friends, so the plans are tiny too. No trials, no tiers
      that punish you for growing a readership.
    </p>

    <div class="pricing">
      <div class="plan">
        <div class="plan-name">Circle</div>
        <div class="price">Free<small>invite-only</small></div>
        <p class="plan-desc">For people we know, and people they know. The full thing, at no cost.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Up to 3 sites</li>
          <li>Custom domains</li>
          <li>Preview branches</li>
          <li>Community workspace</li>
        </ul>
        <a class="plan-cta" href="#cta">Request invite</a>
      </div>

      <div class="plan featured">
        <div class="plan-name">Keeper</div>
        <div class="price">$6<small>/ month</small></div>
        <p class="plan-desc">
          For the slightly more prolific. Unlimited sites, private repos, and the quiet
          analytics panel.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Unlimited sites</li>
          <li>Private repositories</li>
          <li>Extended history (90 days)</li>
          <li>Access control on previews</li>
          <li>Honest analytics</li>
        </ul>
        <a class="plan-cta" href="#cta">Start keeping</a>
      </div>

      <div class="plan">
        <div class="plan-name">Coven</div>
        <div class="price">$18<small>/ month</small></div>
        <p class="plan-desc">
          For small groups sharing a publication. Shared authorship, shared domains, one bill.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Up to 8 members</li>
          <li>Shared identity & authorship</li>
          <li>Role-based access</li>
          <li>Domain groups</li>
          <li>Priority build lane</li>
        </ul>
        <a class="plan-cta" href="#cta">Gather the group</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
